reviews: Lovely Boutique Hotel in great area of Paris (not too touristy).Small but very charming and comfortable, with attentive staff. We would stay again and think it is ideal for couples or small set of friends who want to experience Paris without the tourist crush.

We traveled with our adult children. The location was perfect for us- a vibrant and interesting area. Everyone was happy with the shopping, atmosphere, bars etc . The hotel was sophisticated and homely. The rooms were bright and comfortable with lovely Clarins bathroom products. The breakfast was delicious and refined. All the staff were attentive, efficient and friendly. We’ve stayed in Paris many times in the main tourist areas, but we would all definitely return to this hotel. Loved it!

A special spot in the 3rd - small boutique hotel in a good location with a lovely staff. White table cloth breakfast in the lounge is delicious and special. Eggs to order, good coffee, juices, croissants, lovely well-thought out buffet. You will be set for your day's adventures!

The room was comfortable and the staff were very kind and attentive. They even reached out ahead to time to confirm what kind of bed we wanted in the room. Even though the street outside is busy, with the window closed all the street noise was blocked out which made for a quiet and peaceful environment. The bathroom especially was very nice with a deep soaking tub. Great location as well. Would stay again.

This was our third stay in La Chambre du Marais, and it was yet another great experience! Well furnished room, neatly decorated and with fresh flowers! A very good breakfast buffet and last not least very friendly and helpful staff.

Location excellent, staff was great, rooms elegant, breakfast very good with New York Times to read - only glitch was no hot showers for 5 days. Tepid water each day, almost cold. That hurt the experience.

Hotel situated in very good location, lots to do immediately around the hotel and close to a underground to travel.
Room was small but ok for one night. The Clarins toiletries were a nice surprise.
We had a room at the front of the hotel which was quite noisy late at night due to the bars at the end of street but not too much of a problem.
The loss of 2 stars is because when we was checking out the hotel tried to charge me again for the night, despite having already paid on booking.com. When doing this they didn’t really show me the amount on the card machine so I could have easily just tapped thinking it was just to cover mini bar costs & city tax. Fortunately I did ask to see the full amount on the card machine and explained I had already paid. This caused slight confusion due to the language barrier, but was eventually sorted. So just worth checking the amount on the card machine rather than just tapping.

Had a lovely stay at La chambre du Marais, perfect location, cozy rooms, good breakfast options and lovely staff that supported with everything you needed! Good for business trips but will definitely come back private as well!

Lovely. Friendly. Comfortable. Elegant. And perfectly located. It’s right where you want to be. The staff was incredibly welcoming and warm. Surrounding cafes were perfect…and a nice walk to the Seine and Louvre!

Thank you so much for a wonderful stay in your beautiful and charming boutique hotel in the heart of the Marais! With their hospitality, passion and professionality, the entire team at La Chambre du Marais made our trip to Paris an unforgettable experience from the very first second and we will be definitely coming back soon!

Ideal location. Lovely reception area and well-appointed rooms. Sumptuous breakfast. The staff members exceed all expectations, always gracious, welcoming, and helpful.Mary, who works in the mornings, and Landis, who works in the evenings, are simply amazing. We will most definitely stay here again--a home away from home.

We had done a lot of research for our stay as it was for a special occasion. Even the pre- arrival email checking to see if they could assist with any queries was thoughtfully put together and responded to promptly.
We received a warm welcome from all staff throughout our stay and really appreciated that we were given a complimentary room upgrade, it was a very kind touch.
We loved that this hotel was small and personable, staff are a credit and key part to the enjoyment of our stay. We found that the hotel was exceptionally clean throughout and really enjoyed the buffet selection.
The perfect stay for us

Friendly and welcoming staff
Comfortable bed and clean room
Great location in the heart of the Marais
Delicious breakfast buffet option
We will certainly be back and stay here again! Thank you for all your hospitality!

This boutique Marais hotel is absolutely lovely. The staff was friendly and very helpful. The room was perfect for my needs. It was quite small, but I did not require much space. It was very clean and comfortable. The view was charming and the location was perfect. Would absolutely stay here again and recommend to anyone visiting paris.

Great location, nice and clean room with a comfortable and large bed. Very friendly and helpful staff. Small, stylish and cozy hotel with a very nice breakfast. Overall perfect for a romantic weekend❤️

It’s located in 3rd district of Le Marais and it’s close to metro stations, shops, and restaurants. I couldn’t been happier with this hotel during our stay in Paris. Everyone was so helpful and service was beyond my expectations with logistics with metro system during labor strike day, reservations with restaurants, and more. And everyone helped us out with smiles. it’s a treasure hotel in Paris. I have stayed at Four Seasons hotels before and this hotel had more personal touch with services and hotel decorations were very intimate. Merci!

We adored this hotel - everything about it was ideal. It was the perfect location from which to explore Paris - plenty of Metro stations nearby but also very easy to walk to many places. The service was friendly and attentive, the room was quiet and comfortable. Breakfast was good value and the French toast was delicious! We will definitely return!

We just had one night here as we transitioned to a longer term rental. The most friendly and helpful staff I have encountered, and believe me I have been all over the world. The room is small but so well laid out, and such high quality that it compensates for the small size.

Wonderful spot in the perfect part of the city. Everything is within walking distance and the local atmosphere is ideal. The choice of local cafes, restaurants and shopping is perfect. Highly recommended for both a couples escape or for business.

Excellent hotel with equal service. Best place to stay in the 3rd, whether for business overnight or vacation with significant other. Located in the heart of the 3rd with all its glory only a short walk away.

I loved this hotel and the staff! From start to finish they were kind, responsive and friendly. The bed was so comfortable- we booked a room with a king size bed and it was worth every penny! Location was the best- close to the subway and of course, we enjoyed walking all over. Special thanks to all the wonderful kind staff! We will be back

We liked the personal atmosphere of the house. The room was elegant and nicely decorated. The bathroom bright and friendly.
Excellent restaurants and lively life are nearby. The location is still quiet and relaxed.

We had a wonderful stay at La Chambre du Marais. This atmospheric hotel is in the perfect location, and we were able to leave the front door and meander all over Paris on footbwith ease. Our room was charming and very comfortable, with every amenity we needed. The hotel staff could not have been more friendly and helpful.

we will come again. we like the location, the atmosphere of the hotel , the decor . the regular rooms are small but efficient. the breakfast is very good. the staff is kind and. 200 characters is too much....

Not my first time here and for sure not my last. Simply the best stay in Paris and for the Le Marais fans. Incredible staff, location and place. La Chambre du Marais keep surprising me for it's amazing services every time.

My girlfriend and I had a wonderful week staying here. The hotel is very nice and clean and the staff are extremely pleasant. The location of this hotel is ideal in La Marais neighborhood. We will be coming back.

We just had such a wonderful stay at this hotel. No detail is left untouched. It is an absolutely beautiful property with the friendliest staff. The rooms (while tiny) are so beautiful and the beds are so comfortable. In a wonderful and fun neighborhood where there is always something going on. This was our "splurge" hotel on our recent vacation and it was such a treat!

From the very first day all the staff were very friendly and helpful. Room was clean. Breakfast was delicious. We had and absolutely wonderful time. The hotel was well situated. If I ever were to visit Paris again, I would definitely stay there again.

We absolutely LOVED our stay at the La Chambre and we haven't stopped talking about how wonderful our stay was at this beautiful boutiquey hotel. We highly recommend you stay at La Chambre. The staff goes above and beyond to make your stay a memorable visit. The rooms are adorable and quaint and the bathroom with the heated towels are better than any other hotel we stayed at in Europe. THANK YOU for such an AMAZING experience. We can't wait to come back and visit. And THANK YOU for the incredible Nougat candy you left in our room after I raved about how delicious Nougat tasted!!!

We were holidaying from Australia with family and spent two days in Paris - our family stayed in an apartment nearby but my wife and I decided to stay separately in a hotel and chose La Chambre du Marais from the Trip Advisor site. The hotel was simply superb! From the very intimate reception area and welcoming glass on wine to our beautifully appointed bedroom on the 5th floor, this hotel is quality all the way. The staff were very friendly and helpful - on our first night we were directed to a very fine French restaurant within 5 minutes walk of the hotel. The hotel rates are not cheap and that reflects in the overall quality of this hotel. For anyone who likes to stay in quality places, La Chambre du Marais is the perfect place and we could not recommend this hotel more highly.

Such a comfortable and luxurious sanctuary in the middle of Le Marais district! The rooms are tastefully decorated, unique, and comfortable. It’s also clear that the staff go out of their way to make sure guests are comfortable and happy. Had a wonderful stay and would highly recommend them to anyone!

Overloaded decoration in the common parts but also in the room,
beautiful quality bedding but too high,
We wanted a quiet stay but between the questions of the reception service and the cleaning service and the breakfast service,
we like quietness and we were disappointed to have to speak with all the staff, it was not our choice

We loved our stay at La Chambre du Marais - a cute and cozy boutique hotel, located within walking distance from lots of shops, cafes and art galleries (as well as some of the major Paris sights). The hotel staff was friendly and helpful. We would stay again!

This hotel has a very friendly staff willing to help with any requests. Breakfast was done well and staff very attentive. The room was large for a Paris hotel with a great shower. We will definitely be back and recommend to others.

We absolutely loved this hotel! Everything about was perfect - comfortable lobby, luxurious room, lovely location for exploring The Marias, and very attentive staff. We cannot find anything to fault it on.

Great boutique hotel wonderful location and surrounded by many nice restaurants.
The staff are amazing nothing is too much trouble to ensure your every need is catered for.
The room we stayed in was super clean and the bed very comfortable along with Clarins products very nice touch. We will return.

Quaint, clean, beautiful, well taken care of. If I hadn't had to leave I would not have. I was trying to think of ways to stay longer. I will be back and bring friends and family. The neighborhood is something really special as well.

Best stay ever in Paris so far! Hotel is in great condition, boutique and chic. Very well decorated with taste. Safe, clean and cozy. Hotel is in great location, close to many attractions in Le Marais area, such as center Pompidou, musee of pablo Picasso, musee of Carnavalet, maison of Victor Hugo etc. in walking distance to Louvre as well. Also it’s one of best shopping area as well for individual designers and buyer shops. Breakfast was tasty, exactly what I needed to prepare me for a busy day touring around in Paris. And most most importantly, great and lovely staff!!! The crew made me felt at home, super kind, welcoming, helpful, and efficient. Faby is always at the hotel in the morning and at late night when you needed him, working too hard! Everyone else is also lovely, always making sure that I got what I needed and happily to offer help and advices. One of the most important reasons for me to come back to this hotel again in coming years for sure. Highly recommend!! Thumbs up! Thank you team Le Chambre Du Marais! Made my trip in Paris very pleasant and memorable!

My stay at the Chambre du Marais was very pleasant. The hotel is a charming boutique hotel on a quiet side street in the Le Marais, but also close to main streets and easily reachable by public transport. The staff was exceptionally friendly and helpful and there was great attention for detail on their part and in all aspects related to the running of this hotel.

The hotel was amazing. Great location. The hotel bed was the most comfortable hotel bed I've ever slept in. This was my first trip solo to Paris and I felt very safe in this neighborhood. Will definitely be back.

Went for business trip, would stay again for sure. Lovely staff, very attentive and good help with anything you need. Yes the rooms are small, but all of them are in Paris and it isn’t too small. I’ll be back!

You won’t go wrong by staying in this hotel. The service is outstanding. The room, though small, was very comfortable. The beds were very comfortable. There is a restaurant below but the windows are very soundproof. Breakfast is delicious. The location is very good in the Haute Marais.

We loved our stay and will be back! Staff was wonderful and rooms are comfortable and beautifully decorated. The location cannot be beat as you are in the best neighborhood for restaurants, bars and boutique shopping.

This is a very nice hotel in a great location in Le Marais. The staff is friendly, helpful and charming. The lobby is tiny, sexy and cozy. Lots of competition in Paris, but I would recommend this hotel very strongly for someone who doesn't need a lot of extra space or extras in general.

After a long hiatus in international travel it was an absolute pleasure for us to stay at this hotel. From checkin we were told this is your home for 8 days , welcome.
The staff were beautiful people, warm, engaging, interesting and beyond helpful.
Yes the rooms are small BUT this is an historic hotel in an historic area , you want big you go to a soul less large chain hotel company.
Lovely Clarins products were in the rooms, a small box of nougat and on the second night flowers.
Breakfast is in the intimate lounge on entry. A delicious small array of morsels greeted us each morning , home made cakes, cheeses , charcuterie, nuts, dried fruits, eggs , fresh OJ.
Perfectly located to everything , do yourself a favour and walk , weather permitting , so much is lost on underground travel . Lovely walks in the area free, and paid for. Check out Paris by mouth blog for the low down on restaurants and foodie walks.
Elegantly curated lounge / lobby, light jazz, relaxing ambiance. Sound proof aircon rooms a big plus.
Thank-you Lucien, Fabi, Alicia, Yanes , selwa and all the staff for a lovely stay. We have visited Paris many times , this is we will come back to.
Merci pour tout x

Le Chambre du Marais is a lovely boutique hotel with a great location. The room was great, with a comfortable bed, a modern bathroom and nice amenities. The lobby/eating area had a charming decor. The staff are friendly and helpful.

What a fabulous hotel in an excellent location. We had two rooms - a double and a superior twin with breakfast. The team were faultless and the rooms were great. A choice of metro stations to help explore, but you could arrive here and never have to leave the area. Beds were super comfortable, Clarins toiletries in the bathrooms. Unobtrusive but responsive and friendly service. We would not hesitate to stay here again and recommend it to others.

This hotel and their staff were amazing. I plan to stay here whenever I come to Paris. I will recommend this place with complete confidence. The hotel is charming, the room's decor is tasteful and clean and the location is quintessential Paris. I felt very comfortable and safe and in good hands.

We chose this hotel based on the glowing reviews here on TripAdvisor, not just with regard to the location but also the exceptional service.

Our stay, however, was negatively impacted by a general water cut in the district. While I fully understand that these things happen, my main criticism is that the hotel did not directly inform us, including at check-in. We instead learned about the water cut from a general notice in the elevator (which we could have easily missed should we have taken the stairs). When we then specifically asked about the water cut, we were told that the hotel and staff had been made aware of the water cut a full week prior.

In instances such as these, I would expect a hotel that purports to ensure a comfortable stay to have reached out to its guests as a courtesy. We could have then made the decision to cancel our reservation if we so desired. I will unfortunately not be choosing this hotel on future trips and/or recommending it to others for this reason.

Few channel choices on TV,
room too small to feel good,
bad wifi connection when I had an important poker tournament but all night the connection came then stopped, i lost a max , not good value and i will never come back

After a two-plus year-imposition on travel abroad with all the pandemic regulations and restrictions (some quite silly), we returned to Paris and our favorite hotel therein. It didn’t disappoint. Service, quality of room and location all remain excellent and highly recommended.

This property is an eclipsed jewel in a city of emblematic brands. It’s location is perfect for those who prefer to dwell amongst locals, shop for unique, artisan items, dine in some of the city’s lesser known bests, and have excellent metro transportation to see beyond it. Some of the greatest sites are within walking distance: Picasso Musée, Place des Vosges, République, Oberkampf, Centre Pompidou, Isle Cité to name a few. Staff well organized and versed, atmosphere is meticulously neat and tidy; newer hotel with lots of elegance that evokes a sense of yesteryear, refined.

This beautifully appointed hotel is a real jewel in the Marais. Gorgeous decor and details. Extremely helpful and welcoming hosts. Well located amidst a broad variety of restaurants and shops. We enjoyed our very cozy and comfortable room with its marble bathroom. And, despite all the activity in the Marais, it was very quiet during the night. We would definitely go there again.

A few nights in this hotel during a congress in Paris, the location was convenient for my appointments, but the room was too small when I had chosen a suite, decoration too old and too busy, I had chosen this hotel in relation to the excellent comments but I was really disappointed because small room but too high prices

This was my fourth time at this gorgeous property - beautiful rooms with comfy beds, generous delicious breakfast, spotlessly clean, kind and helpful staff and an excellent location in the Marais. Perfect.

I love La Chambre du Marais. This was my second stay and I would return without hesitation. Great location. Easy walk to all the sights. Beautiful small hotel, comfortable room, and spacious bath. Love the ornate french decor! Staff was available 24/7 to answer questions and help with any issues.

The rooms were nice and quaint. The hotel is very clean. The staff is very attentive. The hotel is conveniently located in the heart of the city. It is very expensive. It is the most expensive hotel I have ever stayed at in 60 years.

The hotel was overall fine and we had a pleasant stay. However, when you are comparing the size of the Pierre room with other hotels (by square metre space), just be aware that the reduced head height / sloping ceiling means that much of the room is not useable space. We are both relatively tall, meaning that we constantly had to be watching out for the reduced head height throughout the room (even above the loo). So, whilst this room is advertised (and priced) as a suite, it's actually quite a small and compromised room because of the head height.

an excellent small hotel in a great location in the northern Marais, not far from the Place de la Republic.Have stayed here now for the 7th time within the last few years, so that should speak volumes along. Well-appointed rooms, friendly and helpful staff, a delicious breakfast served in an elegant setting. Can highly recommend.

It was lovely in every aspect. The staff attentive and welcoming. Well located to many of Paris sights with a nice walk. Easy walk to great resturants. The bathroom was beautiful with big shower and great water pressure Thank you. Will highly recommend

We selected this hotel to be able to experience the Paris vibe, cafés, restaurant choices and location to visit the sites. The staff were excellent as was the included breakfast. We were able to walk or get to public transportation easily to visit the various sites we wanted to see.

We chose the Chambre for its location and it didn’t disappoint. We walked to the Picasso Museum, Norte Dame and the Tuileries (after getting hot chocolate from Angelina’s). We also managed to eat fantastic falafel at L’AS.

Amazing hotel! The staff, location, clean , comfort of the beds & bathroom, breakfast was delicious! I highly recommend ! next time in Paris will definitely book this hotel again. It is relatively close to metro station but if you are looking to be in the heart of the touristy areas it is not for you.

When asked for feedback upon leaving all I could say is “nothing but positive”. The location is right on the middle of the Marais. The rooms were clean and well appointed. The breakfast was filling and relaxed. At the end of each day of sightseeing we returned to friendly staff and a spotless room. I would 100% stay here again when in Paris.

Charming hotel close to local bars and restaurants. Very quiet at night. Room was spacious with an excellent shower. High quality linens and decor. Breakfast was wonderful lovely selection of bread, croissants fruit, yoghurt and eggs. Staff were lovely, extremely helpful and welcoming. Highly recommend.

We stayed at La Chambre du Marais for a week, in connection with our first visit to the city of cities, Paris. La Chambre du Marais is a beautiful and charming little boutique hotel located in the enchanting 3rd arrondissement, Haut-Marais. There is many small streets with hip cafes, restaurants, delicatessens, hidden pearls as well as local and international shops. It is easy to get around the city to experience the many landmarks Paris has to offer.
Before arrival, we were contacted by La Chambre du Marais, where they offered to help with booking activities, visits, tours, and attractions, so that we could get the most out of our stay.
On our arrival we were welcomed by the staff and offered a beverage while we were checked in and our luggage was taken to our room.
The breakfast is exquisite with small variations during the week and is absolutely recommendable. It is possible to choose the coffee/tea you prefer and whether you want soft-boiled eggs, omelettes or scrambled eggs for your breakfast.
Throughout our visit, we have been greeted by a helpful and friendly staff who have made us feel at home. We can highly recommend this small hotel and hope to use it again on future visits to Paris

Everything at La Chambre du Marais exceeded our expectations. The location was perfect, the hotel and its rooms were stylish and comfortable, and the staff was superb - taking care of every detail. Highly recommend this gem in the heart of Marais!

Stayed with my wife and 3 year old daughter. Loved the comfort of the entire hotel. Felt like our own private apartment in the heart of the Marais. Everyone was courteous and helpful. The vibe was chill and relaxed. I would and plan to staying here again.

The staff gave us a very warm welcome. It has been a very pleasant stay. from th beginning on. The hotel is situated ideal for exploring the many sights of Paris. Also there are many restaurants in a short walking distance where you can spent the evenings.

When we arrived on our first morning, Lucien greeted us by saying “Welcome home” and it indeed that is how it felt. This hotel is a small gem. It is in a
Quiet neighborhood which is walkable to busy streets of shops and restaurants. The rooms are impeccably clean and comfortable. The breakfast is perfect with fresh pastries, fruits and cooked to order eggs each morning. But the best thing about the hotel is the staff. Everyone was gracious, friendly and helpful. I cannot say enough good things about this hotel and we can’t wait to return

everything about this hotel is magical! We always stay here. The staff is gracious, warm and friendly, the breakfast is fresh and delicious. The rooms ate lovely, clean and welcoming and the location is safe and centrally located!

This is an unequivocally lovely hotel in Le Marais. The hotel itself is conveniently near several restaurants, boutique stores, and bars. Our room was stylish and impeccably clean. Staff was professional, yet very friendly and accommodating. The daily breakfast array was fresh and delicious. I note that a reviewer below stated they were at the hotel during the recent heat wave and had issues with their air conditioning temperature. I wonder if this was brought to the staff’s attention? My stay at the hotel was also during the heat wave and I had no such problem. Based on my interactions with the staff though, I have no doubts that they would have rectified the problem immediately if I had.

This hotel offers French style, comfortable accomodations and a most hospitable and professional staff. They were always warm and friendly in helping us with directions, recommendations and questions. The rooms are so comfortable and luxurious. The hotel is well located for travelers interested in strolling the stores and cafes of the Marais neighborhood and beyond. I would highly recommend this fabulous hotel and plan to return myself.

We absolutely loved the location of this hotel - it was walkable to everything. It was clean and comfortable and I cannot wait to return!! The staff were amazing as well - always available should we need anything. Highly recommend this property!

This is a small boutique hotel centrally located in the Marais district. The service is superb. The staff knows each person and her special requirements if any. The quality of the food presented for the breakfast buffet is just awesome. It is new and very clean. We had the Catherine suite with a sitting area as well as a living room and hallway closets. The bathroom is small and a bit awkward in design, but the shower is roomy. Our suite is on the 4th floor facing Rue des Archives. The traffic noise can get very loud at night. Overall, it is a good place if you are looking for a hotel in Marais.

We absolutely LOVED our stay at La Chambre du Marais. Perfect location, perfect accommodations, perfect breakfast, perfect staff. The breakfast was the best part to be honest. Fresh baked goods and pasteries, deliciousI wish we could always stay in this hotel!!

We had come during the heat wave in Paris, warm welcome from the staff, clean and good-sized room, we were surprised that the temperature in the room was so high but we thought that the staff had just turned on the air conditioning,
but at bedtime we couldn't lower the temperature in the room,
we hadn't been able to sleep it was so hot, not even an apology from the manager

I stayed for a couple of days as a solo traveler. The hotel is heaven. Location is brilliant and the rooms are luxurious. The staff was so polite and friendly and helpful. I absolutely would recommend this hotel and hope to visit again soon!

We were in the neighborhood and decided to try it. Exceptionally good service and their suggestions were delicious, even though I am very meticulous. I loved the paté and a "secret sauce" to dip in the bread.

We can't say enough good things about the staff and our stay at this hotel. They have a superb concierge service that started weeks before we arrived. The staff was courteous, knowledgeable, friendly and attentive. The breakfasts were sumptuous and always fresh. The rooms were exquisitely appointed and extraordinarily comfortable. This is a gem in the heart of the Marais. Can't wait to return.

This is a beautiful small hotel in the Marais. I have stayed there twice and was impressed both times by the excellent service and attention to detail. The rooms are elegant, not huge but very tastefully decorated and comfortable.

It is absolutely the perfect hotel in Paris! Everything is well thought of! Every detail…. It even have the Perfect breakfast!
Everything is fresh and perfect!
The standard room is small… but very clean and pleasant !
We deeply recommend

Wonderful staff, but room was a bit smaller than expected. Also, housekeeping had to be reminded to attend to the room and to replace free beverages daily. We stayed for 10 nights so were given a free breakfast. Nice touch!

Great cosy boutique hotel in the Marais. Amazing feel as soon as you enter the hotel, very warm welcome, very tasteful decor. Beds are so comfortable ! Feels like you are coming home!I will be back! This will be my hotel in Paris forever!

This hotel is a gem in the heart of Paris. You can walk to all the major sites. I can’t imagine I’ll ever stay anywhere else. The staff is excellent. The rooms are excellent. The location is excellent. It’s simply the best.

We loved this hotel and would absolutely stay there again. We spent 6 nights in a deluxe double room and the extra space was wonderful. From the beautiful daily breakfast to the comfortable beds, they think of everything for your comfort. The staff was very helpful with transportation needs and helping with departure Covid testing. This has been the nicest hotel I’ve stayed at in Paris and I’m looking forward to the next trip.

I loved my stay here, found the room so comfortable and pretty and quiet even though it was in a busting neighborhood. The service was great, the bed so comfortable and the location perfect. I will definitely stay here again!

To quote another reviewer, I hesitate to advertise this amazing hotel because I want to keep it a secret from everyone else!
The service was amazing! The staff were so kind and went out of their way to assist! I apologize if I don't spell their names correctly and I can't remember everyone's name but shout out to Lia and Lucia and the rest! From the moment we arrived, they took our luggage and brought it to our room which wasn't quite ready and we arrived before noon so we just wanted to drop off our luggage. They served us coffee and made us feel very welcome. They were always available to answer questions and assist with transportation reservations.
Lobby - charming and beautiful! Very clean! Board games set up if you want to chill and hang out! Someone is always on duty literally behind the scenes. Felt very safe and comfortable.
Rooms - the building is a typical European historical building with a smaller lift (2 people max) and a narrow stairwell but very easy to maneuver to get to your floor.
Our room was perfect! It had windows that swing in to allow the feeling of a Juliet Balcony while you relax in your room. Bed was roomy and very comfortable. Bathroom was great - huge tub and shower! Toilet room was also nice with a very small sink. Plenty of closets.
Suggestions: for the small sink in the bathroom, do not turn it on fully as it will spray and get all over the floor. Perhaps leave a small bath mat below the sink to absorb the puddle in the toilet room.
Suggestions: add a few more towel hooks. The heated towel bar is great however would benefit from additional smaller hooks to hang other towels or clothes that need some airing out.
Did not discover the luggage rack under the bed until our last day.
Beautifully designed rooms. Bathroom contains everything you need. The closet also has a hidden beautiful box with items you may have forgotten for your trip. Bathrobes and slippers were a nice addition!
Contrary to other reviewers, I believe they did refill our small shower gel and shampoo.
When we arrived there was a beautiful box of handmade carmels on our bed.
In addition, they arranged for a surprise gift for me that was ordered by my sibling for my birthday. They served us champagne on ice with a dozen roses in a beautiful vase!
I can't wait to go back.
Yes, it is pricey but it is a very special boutique hotel.
Location is fabulous. You can walk everywhere. Great restaurants - located near corner of Rue des Archives and Rue de Bretagne.

Good note:There is no smoking in the hotel - which is great!

Paris Note: However, beware that throughout Paris, it seems like everyone is smoking at every outdoor cafe!

We stayed here four nights in late April and it was perfect. The hotel has a relax boutique feel to it while being luxurious at the same time. The bed was great, staff was on top of everything, and the included breakfast each day was perfect. Highly recommend!

Beautifully decorated boutique hotel. Delicious breakfast options. Great location for seeing the district and people watching. There are many dining and shopping options available. It’s not from rail Staff is very friendly and personable .

The hotel is situated in a lively but still peaceful area with park, cafes etc. The hotel itself has a 'classical' layout, and nicely decorated rooms with excellent bathroom facilities. Breakfast is very good, and staff very helpful so you feel very welcome

we stayed at La Chambre du Marais for 3 days, a family of 6 (2 Adults and 4 children), the hotel is beautiful, the stuff is amazing, the location is great and we enjoyed every minute. we recommend the hotel, for couples and for families, we sure we will be back visiting the hotel.

Picking a hotel in Paris can be very overwhelming so, please, reach out to me if you have questions and know you can book this hotel with confidence.

If you can afford this hotel and like boutique experiences, look no further. There is no front desk staff but the staff is there to welcome you all hours in the beautiful foyer you step in from the street. Leah was my favorite person there. So helpful and sweet. They all are very attentive to every need.

The rooms are beautiful and cozy and the bed is absurdly comfortable. There is also a Nespresso machine, a towel warmer, Frette sheets. They do need more drawer space for clothes but a small detail I'm happy to overlook.

The breakfast is lovely if you want to take it slow in the morning.

Wonderful.

We were looking for the perfect place to stay on our trip to Paris and we found it! A gem of a hotel - boutique - in the Marais, a beautiful and centrally located neighborhood. Safe, fun and interesting. I wouldn't think of staying anywhere else. The room was lovely and comfortable, the staff was amazing and helpful, breakfast was delicious and plentiful. Highly recommend!

It’s a gift when you have the greatest hospitality in the lovely Marais. The hotel and her staff made our days in Paris great.
The location is perfect. You walk out of the door and the buzzle is just around the corner. Top!

Thank you for a memorable days, amazing stay and great service and attention for all details! The staff was very attentive and gave us good feeling , making our stay wonderful! We will definitely come back to stay again here! Thank you so much!

Everything - the staff, the room, the ambience, the location (fantastic location), amenities - was fabulous. I had the smallest room in the hotel as I was travelling solo and even then the room was more than adequately sized for me and extremely clean and comfortable and chic. Couldn’t recommend this place enough, I’ll surely live here on my next trip to paris

We love this hotel and wish we could have stayed longer. Everything was perfect - very high quality and and very special - and cosy and friendly. A real home-from-home - with luxury!. And the location is perfect - right in the middle of our favourite area of Paris. We will definitely come to stay again, and will recommend to friends.

The staff were extremely welcoming and accommodating. The location was excellent. I would recommend getting the breakfast, it was a great start to the day and delicious. The rooms were clean and comfortable. Our experience was 10/10.

Great location. Really get the local Parisian vibe. Rooms are very well furnished and the free unlimited tea and coffee are amazing. Staff very helpful and easy going. Spaces are small but it is compensated with the high quality hotel amenities
